def show_class_examples(dataset, num_per_class=10):
    class_0 = []
    class_1 = []
    
    for image, label in dataset:
        label = int(label[0])
        if label == 0 and len(class_0) < num_per_class:
            class_0.append(image)
        elif label == 1 and len(class_1) < num_per_class:
            class_1.append(image)
        if len(class_0) == num_per_class and len(class_1) == num_per_class:
            break

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, num_per_class, figsize=(num_per_class * 1.5, 3))
    for i in range(num_per_class):
        axes[0, i].imshow(class_0[i][0], cmap='gray')
        axes[0, i].axis('off')
        axes[0, i].set_title("Label 0")

        axes[1, i].imshow(class_1[i][0], cmap='gray')
        axes[1, i].axis('off')
        axes[1, i].set_title("Label 1")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig('class_examples.pdf')
    plt.show()

show_class_examples(train_dataset)

Preprocessing – balancing data by undersampling¶

Undersampling was chosen to align with the research hypothesis, which focuses on comparing classical and quantum models on small datasets. By selecting an equal number of samples per class, we ensure a fair comparison without introducing bias from class imbalance.

In [7]:
def balance_dataset(dataset, samples_per_class=147):
    class_0_indices = [i for i, (_, label) in enumerate(dataset) if int(label[0]) == 0]
    class_1_indices = [i for i, (_, label) in enumerate(dataset) if int(label[0]) == 1]

    selected_0 = class_0_indices[:samples_per_class]
    selected_1 = class_1_indices[:samples_per_class]

    indices = selected_0 + selected_1
    balanced_subset = Subset(dataset, indices)
    return balanced_subset

balanced_train_dataset = balance_dataset(train_dataset)
print(f"Balanced dataset size: {len(balanced_train_dataset)}")

Train and evaluate functions¶

In [9]:
def train_model(model, train_loader, val_loader, device, model_path, classical_gmean=None, criterion=None, optimizer=None, epochs=50, patience=5):

    model.to(device)
    is_quantum = any('q_layer' in name for name, _ in model.named_modules())

    if criterion is None:
        criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()

    if optimizer is None:
        lr = 1e-5 if is_quantum else 1e-4
        optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=lr)

    best_gmean = 0.0
    patience_counter = 0
    best_model_state = copy.deepcopy(model.state_dict())
    saved_at_least_once = False

    for epoch in range(epochs):
        model.train()
        running_loss = 0.0
        for images, labels in train_loader:
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.squeeze().long().to(device)
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            outputs = model(images)
            loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
            loss.backward()
            torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), max_norm=1.0)
            optimizer.step()
            running_loss += loss.item()

        avg_train_loss = running_loss / len(train_loader)

        # === Validation ===
        model.eval()
        val_loss = 0.0
        val_preds, val_labels, all_probs = [], [], []
        with torch.no_grad():
            for images, labels in val_loader:
                images, labels = images.to(device), labels.squeeze().long().to(device)
                outputs = model(images)
                loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
                val_loss += loss.item()

                probs = torch.softmax(outputs, dim=1)[:, 1]
                preds = torch.argmax(outputs, dim=1)

                val_preds.extend(preds.cpu().numpy())
                all_probs.extend(probs.cpu().numpy())
                val_labels.extend(labels.cpu().numpy())

        avg_val_loss = val_loss / len(val_loader)
        auc = roc_auc_score(val_labels, all_probs)

        # G-mean
        cm = confusion_matrix(val_labels, val_preds, normalize='true')
        gmean = np.sqrt(np.prod(cm.diagonal()))

        print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs} | Train Loss: {avg_train_loss:.4f} | "
              f"Val Loss: {avg_val_loss:.4f} | G-mean: {gmean:.4f} | AUC: {auc:.4f}")

        if gmean > best_gmean:
            best_gmean = gmean
            best_model_state = copy.deepcopy(model.state_dict())
            torch.save(best_model_state, model_path)
            saved_at_least_once = True
            patience_counter = 0
        else:
            patience_counter += 1

        if is_quantum and saved_at_least_once:
            if patience_counter >= patience:
                if classical_gmean is not None and best_gmean > classical_gmean:
                    print(f"Early stopping at epoch {epoch+1}: G-mean {best_gmean:.4f} > classical {classical_gmean:.4f}")
                    break
                else:
                    patience_counter = 0

    model.load_state_dict(torch.load(model_path))
    print(f"Best model restored from: {model_path}")
    return model
In [10]:
def evaluate_model(model, test_loader, device, title="Model", color='tab:purple'):

    model.eval()
    all_preds = []
    all_labels = []
    all_probs = []

    with torch.no_grad():
        for images, labels in test_loader:
            images = images.to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            probs = torch.softmax(outputs, dim=1)[:, 1]
            preds = torch.argmax(outputs, dim=1)
            all_probs.extend(probs.cpu().numpy())
            all_preds.extend(preds.cpu().numpy())
            all_labels.extend(labels.numpy())

    ConfusionMatrixDisplay.from_predictions(
        all_labels,
        all_preds,
        display_labels=["Zoliwy", "agodny/Zdrowy"],
    )
    plt.title(f"Macierz pomyek - {title}")
    plt.grid(False)
    plt.show()

    print("Classification report:")
    print(classification_report(all_labels, all_preds, target_names=["Zoliwy", "agodny/Zdrowy"]))

    recall_0 = recall_score(all_labels, all_preds, pos_label=0)
    recall_1 = recall_score(all_labels, all_preds, pos_label=1)
    gmean = np.sqrt(recall_0 * recall_1)

    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(all_labels, all_probs)
    roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"AUC = {roc_auc:.2f}", color=color)
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--', label='Random')
    plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
    plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    plt.title(f"ROC Curve  {title}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
    plt.show()

    acc = accuracy_score(all_labels, all_preds)
    f1 = f1_score(all_labels, all_preds, pos_label=0)
    precision = precision_score(all_labels, all_preds)
    recall = recall_score(all_labels, all_preds)

    results_df = pd.DataFrame({
        "Metric": ["Accuracy", "F1-score", "Precision", "Recall", "G-mean", "AUC"],
        "Value": [acc, f1, precision, recall, gmean, roc_auc]
    })

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 3))
    sns.barplot(data=results_df, x="Metric", y="Value", color=color)
    plt.ylim(0, 1)
    plt.title(f"Performance Metrics  {title}")
    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
    plt.show()

    return results_df

class ResNet18_1Channel(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_classes=2):
        super().__init__()
        self.model = models.resnet18(weights=None)

        # Input channels to 1
        self.model.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(
            in_channels=1,
            out_channels=64,
            kernel_size=7,
            stride=2,
            padding=3,
            bias=False
        )

        self.model.fc = nn.Linear(self.model.fc.in_features, n_classes)

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.model(x)

Quantum-enhanced ResNet18 - end¶

In [13]:
n_qubits = 4

dev = qml.device("default.qubit", wires=n_qubits, shots=None)

@qml.qnode(dev, interface="torch")
def quantum_circuit(inputs, weights):
    qml.templates.AngleEmbedding(inputs, wires=range(n_qubits))
    qml.templates.BasicEntanglerLayers(weights, wires=range(n_qubits))
    return [qml.expval(qml.PauliZ(i)) for i in range(n_qubits)]

weight_shapes = {"weights": (2, n_qubits)}
QuantumLayer = qml.qnn.TorchLayer(quantum_circuit, weight_shapes)


from torchvision import models
import torch.nn as nn

class QuantumResNet18(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_qubits=4, n_classes=2):
        super().__init__()
        self.model = models.resnet18(weights=None)

        # Input channels to 1
        self.model.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(
            in_channels=1,
            out_channels=64,
            kernel_size=7,
            stride=2,
            padding=3,
            bias=False
        )

        self.model.fc = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(self.model.fc.in_features, n_qubits),
            QuantumLayer,
            nn.Linear(n_qubits, n_classes)
        )

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.model(x)

device = torch.device("cpu")
q_model = QuantumResNet18(n_qubits=n_qubits).to(device)
print(f"Quantum-enhanced ResNet18 using {device}")
torch.save(q_model.state_dict(), "quantum_end_resnet18_start.pt")

Quantum-enhanced ResNet18 - mid¶

In [15]:
class QuantumLayer(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_qubits=4, depth=2):
        super().__init__()
        self.n_qubits = n_qubits
        self.depth = depth
        self.dev = qml.device("default.qubit", wires=n_qubits)

        @qml.qnode(self.dev, interface="torch")
        def circuit(inputs, weights):
            qml.templates.AngleEmbedding(inputs, wires=range(n_qubits))
            qml.templates.BasicEntanglerLayers(weights, wires=range(n_qubits))
            return [qml.expval(qml.PauliZ(i)) for i in range(n_qubits)]

        weight_shapes = {"weights": (depth, n_qubits)}
        self.q_layer = qml.qnn.TorchLayer(circuit, weight_shapes)

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.q_layer(x)
In [16]:
class QuantumMidResNet18(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_qubits=4, quantum_layer_depth=2):
        super().__init__()
        resnet = models.resnet18(weights=None)

        # Input channels to 1
        resnet.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(
            in_channels=1,
            out_channels=64,
            kernel_size=7,
            stride=2,
            padding=3,
            bias=False
        )

        self.backbone = nn.Sequential(
            resnet.conv1,
            resnet.bn1,
            resnet.relu,
            resnet.maxpool,
            resnet.layer1,
            resnet.layer2,
            resnet.layer3
        )

        self.reduction = nn.Sequential(
            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1)),
            nn.Flatten(),
            nn.Linear(256, n_qubits)
        )

        self.q_layer = QuantumLayer(n_qubits=n_qubits, depth=quantum_layer_depth)
        self.classifier = nn.Linear(n_qubits, 2)

    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.backbone(x)
        x = self.reduction(x)
        x = self.q_layer(x)
        x = self.classifier(x)
        return x

device = torch.device("cpu")
q_model = QuantumMidResNet18().to(device)
print(f"Quantum-enhanced ResNet18 using {device}")
torch.save(q_model.state_dict(), "quantum_mid_resnet18_start.pt")

In [18]:
def compare_models(results_classical, results_quantum, model_names):
    merged = pd.merge(results_classical, results_quantum, on="Metric", suffixes=(f"_{model_names[0]}", f"_{model_names[1]}"))

    merged["Difference"] = merged[f"Value_{model_names[1]}"] - merged[f"Value_{model_names[0]}"]
    merged["Relative (%)"] = 100 * merged["Difference"] / merged[f"Value_{model_names[0]}"]
    merged["Direction"] = merged["Difference"].apply(lambda x: "Improved" if x > 0 else ("Worsened" if x < 0 else "No Change"))

    return merged

def plot_model_comparison(comparison_df, model_names):
    metrics = comparison_df["Metric"]

    values_classical = comparison_df[f"Value_{model_names[0]}"]
    values_quantum = comparison_df[f"Value_{model_names[1]}"]
    diffs = comparison_df["Relative (%)"]

    x = np.arange(len(metrics))
    width = 0.35

    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))

    ax1.bar(x - width/2, values_classical, width, label=model_names[0], alpha=0.8, color='tab:purple')
    ax1.bar(x + width/2, values_quantum, width, label=model_names[1], alpha=0.8, color='tab:pink')

    ax1.set_ylabel("Warto metryki")
    ax1.set_title(f"Porwnanie wartoci metryk dla modeli {model_names[0]} i {model_names[1]} ")
    ax1.set_xticks(x)
    ax1.set_xticklabels(metrics, rotation=45)
    ax1.legend()

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
    plt.show()

def plot_model_comparison_three_models_fixed(df, model_names, colors):
    metrics = df["Metric"]
    x = np.arange(len(metrics))
    width = 0.25

    values_baseline = df["Value_Klasycznego_x"]
    values_q_end = df["Value_Kwantowego (End)"]
    values_q_mid = df["Value_Kwantowego (Mid)"]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))

    ax.bar(x - width, values_baseline, width, label=model_names[0], color=colors[0], alpha=0.8)
    ax.bar(x, values_q_end, width, label=model_names[1], color=colors[1], alpha=0.8)
    ax.bar(x + width, values_q_mid, width, label=model_names[2], color=colors[2], alpha=0.8)

    ax.set_ylabel("Metric value")
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(metrics, rotation=45, ha='right')
    ax.legend()
    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig('model_comparison_three_models.pdf')
    plt.show()
